{"type":"message","id":"7377890b","parentId":"c57d736c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T04:30:11.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📖 **Word of the Day — April 1, 2026**\n\n**Limerence** /ˈlɪm.ər.əns/ — _noun_\n\nA state of intense, involuntary romantic infatuation characterized by obsessive thoughts,渴望 reciprocation, and emotional dependency on another person. Coined by psychologist Dorothy Tennov in 1979.\n\n_Example:_ \"He checked his phone for the fourth time in ten minutes — limerence had a grip on him that logic couldn't break.\""}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775017811627}}
