{"type":"message","id":"3ac0712b","parentId":"45149a4f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T05:56:11.024Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📖 Word of the Day — April 1, 2026\n\n**Hiraeth** (HEER-eyeth) — *n.* A deep, nostalgic longing for a home, a time, or a place that may never have existed. A homesickness for somewhere you can't return to — or that was never real to begin with.\n\n*\"Standing on the hilltop at twilight, she felt a wave of hiraeth — not for the town below, but for the version of it that lived only in her memory.\"*"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775022971024}}
