{"type":"message","id":"0de23063","parentId":"2dcf02a2","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:30:15.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🖤 Afternoon comedy break ⚡\n\n**1. Dark/Edgy:**\nMy therapist said I need to stop romanticizing death.\nSo I started romanticizing life instead.\nNow I'm just disappointed by *everything.*\n\n**2. Workplace:**\nMy boss said \"dress for the job you want, not the job you have.\"\nSo I showed up in pajamas.\nApparently \"professional napper\" wasn't what he meant.\n\n**3. Absurd:**\nI taught my parrot to say \"help, I've been turned into a parrot.\"\nNobody's come to rescue him yet.\nHonestly starting to think people just don't care."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775039415210}}
{"type":"message","id":"229d7001","parentId":"0de23063","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:30:29.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🌙 *Bedtime Story*\n\nIn 1955, a tired woman named Rosa Parks\nboarded a bus in Montgomery, Alabama.\nWhen told to give up her seat — she simply said \"No.\"\nThat one quiet word echoed across an entire nation.\nPeople walked miles instead of riding buses for 381 days.\nNot with violence. Not with anger. Just with patience.\nAnd one day, the highest court in America said:\n\"She was right.\"\n\nSometimes the bravest thing you can do\nis stay seated when the world tells you to move.\n\nSleep well, everyone. Tomorrow's another day to be brave 🖤"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775061029751}}
